components.name: Check and Download Ensembl Mapping Files
components.description: Checks Ensembl FTP for new genomic mapping files and downloads any updates to the S3 raw landing zone.
outputs: updated genomic mapping files in S3 raw landing zone (s3://cqgc-{env}-app-datalake/raw/landing/ensembl/)

components.name: Process Ensembl Mapping with Spark
components.description: Runs a Spark job on Kubernetes to transform the downloaded Ensembl TSV files into structured tables stored in the data lake.
outputs: Processed Ensembl mapping tables in the data lake (e.g., parquet files or Hive tables)

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful completion of the file download task.

connections.purpose: Read raw files and write processed tables

components.name: Slack Notification on DAG Start
components.description: Sends a Slack message when the ETL pipeline is manually triggered.

upstream_policy.description: Runs at the very beginning of the pipeline.

components.name: Slack Notification on Task Failure
components.description: Sends a Slack alert when any task in the pipeline fails.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered by failure callbacks of any task.

components.name: Slack Notification on DAG Completion
components.description: Sends a Slack message when the pipeline completes successfully.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after all pipeline tasks finish without error.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

mapping_types.description: List of Ensembl mapping types to process (canonical, ena, entrez, refseq, uniprot)

s3_bucket_format.description: S3 bucket naming pattern, e.g., cqgc-{env}-app-datalake

s3_key_path.description: S3 key prefix for raw landing zone (raw/landing/ensembl/)

ftp_base_path.description: Base FTP directory for Ensembl files (ftp.ensembl.org/pub/current_tsv/homo_sapiens)

spark_class.description: Fully qualified Spark class to execute (bio.ferlab.datalake.spark3.publictables.ImportPublicTable)

table_name.description: Target table name in data lake (ensembl_mapping)

sources: Ensembl FTP server providing genomic mapping TSV.GZ files (canonical, ena, entrez, refseq, uniprot).
sinks: Processed Ensembl mapping tables stored in the S3 data lake under the processed/ensembl_mapping path.
intermediate_datasets: Spark temporary tables / intermediate Parquet files generated during the Spark job (implicit within the Spark execution environment).
